I have made this exact same recipe for over 45 years, however, over time I have tweaked it a little bit. Delete the allspice, double the powdered ginger, include a generous amount of chopped crystalized ginger, and reduce the hot water by 2 tablespoons, replacing it with fresh ginger juice. I accompany the cake with softly whipped cream and ice cold homemade applesauce. Yes, you now know I'm addicted to gingerbread.

