Rating: 4
Fabulous! I made these in a muffin tin for individual sized cakes & turned them upside down to serve. I heated briefly in the microwave before serving and then topped with sweetened whipped cream, drizzled with a caramel sauce, and sprinkled white chocolate pieces over that. They were wonderful. I also used full flavor molasses but ran out needing about 1/4 cup so I substitued honey for the remainder. I too used heaping measuring spoons of the spices. They had a strong gingerbread flavor which everyone loved. Make this cake! For caramel sauce - 1 stick butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 2 T milk, 1 t vanilla bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute. Adding cold espresso to the whipped cream for a mocha cream would also be great with this.

Rating: 3
I am a novice wedding cake maker that recently used this recipe to rave reviews. A good friend wanted her wedding cake to be all gingerbread so I came to Epicurious because I have never been disapointed...and I wasn't! I followed this recipe exactly and it turned out delicious every time (the only minor adjustments being heaping spoonfulls of each spice listed as opposed to a level measure). Moist, delicious and you really got the gingerbread flavor without it being overpowering like, say, a gingerbread man cookie :) The cake was solid enough for building and stacking - I made a three-tier, double-layer cake to serve approx. 150 people. I didn't hear one complaint and even had a few people pull me aside to tell me it was excellent and tasty! One wedding-goer even said, "I've been to tons of weddings and this is by far the best wedding cake I have ever tasted!" So, if you need a good gingerbread cake recipe look no further - - this is it!

